---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Client portal"
  description="A simple, calm portal for the people your clinicians care for. One-click sign-in by email or text, mobile-first, English and Spanish out of the box."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Client portal"
    title="A portal that respects the client's <em>time and attention.</em>"
    lede="The Praxnote portal is intentionally calm and quick. Clients tap a sign-in link from their email or text — there's no password to remember. It works on a phone the way clients expect a phone to work. Every screen is translated."
  >
    <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request access</a>
  </PageHeader>

  <section class="overview">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="overview-grid">
        <div>
          <h2>What clients can do.</h2>
          <ul class="checks">
            <li>Sign in by tapping a link in their email or text — no password</li>
            <li>See their upcoming appointments, and book new ones against their clinician's availability</li>
            <li>Reschedule or cancel, within the practice's policy</li>
            <li>Send and receive secure messages with their clinician</li>
            <li>Upload intake forms, insurance cards, and completed assessments</li>
            <li>Complete an assessment their clinician assigned (PHQ-9, GAD-7, and others)</li>
            <li>See and pay invoices</li>
            <li>Set up autopay with a saved card</li>
            <li>Switch between English and Spanish (or other languages your practice adds)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mock">
          <div class="mock-card">
            <header>
              <span class="mock-logo">prax<i>note</i></span>
              <span class="badge">EN · ES</span>
            </header>
            <h4>Welcome back, Jordan</h4>
            <p class="muted">You have one upcoming session and one form to complete.</p>
            <ul class="mock-list">
              <li><strong>Tue 3:00 pm</strong> · Dr. Patel · Telehealth</li>
              <li><strong>Form</strong> · Initial intake (8 min)</li>
              <li><strong>Assessment</strong> · PHQ-9 · ready to start</li>
            </ul>
            <button class="btn btn-primary">Complete intake</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="auth alt">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">How clients sign in</p>
        <h2>One-click links. <em>No passwords to remember, lose, or leak.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Praxnote sends each client a single-use sign-in link by email or text. They tap it,
          they're in. No password is created, stored, or asked for — which means there is no
          password for anyone to steal, share, or reuse from another site.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>How sign-in works</h4>
          <ol class="num-list">
            <li>The client requests access, or receives an invitation from their clinician</li>
            <li>Praxnote sends them a single-use link by email or text</li>
            <li>They tap the link, and the portal opens, already signed in</li>
            <li>For clients who use the portal offline (waiting rooms, in transit), the device can keep a private, PIN-locked copy of what they need</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Why this is safer than passwords</h4>
          <p>Most password breaches happen because people reuse the same password across sites. A site that doesn't have a password can't have that problem. There's nothing to remember and nothing to steal.</p>
          <p>For practices that want an extra layer, the portal can be set to require a one-time code by email on every sign-in. SMS codes and authenticator-app codes are coming.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="i18n">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">For clients who don't read in English</p>
        <h2>English and Spanish from day one. <em>More on request.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Every screen of the client portal is translated. English and Spanish ship by default. Practices
          serving clients in other languages can add more, and each client's language preference is
          remembered between visits. Clinician and admin screens stay in English.
        </p>
      </header>

      <ul class="checks">
        <li>The client's language preference is remembered each time they come back</li>
        <li>Additional languages can be added at the practice's request; English is always available</li>
        <li>Every screen is designed for phones — large taps, clear type, calm pacing</li>
        <li>A warm, low-contrast palette designed to meet accessibility standards without feeling clinical</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    eyebrow="See the portal end to end"
    heading="Walk through a client's first day."
    body="From the first sign-in link through their first appointment, first intake, and first assessment — about ten minutes on the walk-through. The shape of the experience your clients will actually have."
    primaryHref="/demo"
    primaryLabel="Book a walk-through"
    secondaryHref="/features/scheduling"
    secondaryLabel="See scheduling"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .overview { padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .overview-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem); align-items: center; }
  .overview-grid h2 { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  @media (max-width: 920px) { .overview-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .mock {
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .mock-card {
    background: var(--surface-card);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 360px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-popover);
  }
  .mock-card header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .mock-logo { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-teal-dark); }
  .mock-logo i { color: var(--brand-teal); font-style: italic; }
  .mock-card h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .mock-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1.25rem 0 1.5rem; display: grid; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .mock-list li { padding: 0.7rem 0.85rem; background: var(--paper-warm); border-radius: var(--radius); font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--stone-700); }
  .mock-list strong { color: var(--brand-teal-dark); margin-right: 0.4rem; }

  .alt { background: var(--paper-warm); border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
  .auth, .i18n { padding: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .section-head { max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .section-head .lede { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .num-list { padding-left: 1.25rem; color: var(--stone-700); }
  .num-list li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .card h4 { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.85rem; }
  .card p { color: var(--stone-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.65; }
</style>
